1602302400.title: Bargain Hunt
1602302400.descr: Natasha Raskin Sharp is in charge today as Bargain Hunt visits the Westpoint Arena near Exeter. Two sisters take on husband and wife as they race against the clock to buy three items in 60 minutes, with Danny Sebastian and Gary Pe keeping the red and blue teams on track. Meanwhile, Natasha learns about a mysterious book from the Far East.

1602305100.title: Bargain Hunt
1602305100.descr: Two teams of amateur antique collectors meet at an antiques fair to compete to make the largest profit from a three hundred pound budget. Once the contestants have done the shopping for their own items, the experts then take any leftover money and go shopping for more antiques which is 'bonus buys'. The teams then have to decide whether or not to take these items to auction.

1602307800.title: DIY SOS: The Big Build
1602307800.descr: Take a family in desperate need of help in their home. Add some local tradesmen, lot's of generosity and a bucket load of community spirit. You've got yourself the recipe for DIY SOS. Nick Knowles, along with him team of home improvement experts, and lot's of happy volunteers from the communities of Britain pitch in to make life changing modifications to the homes of families who need them most.

1602314400.title: Last of the Summer Wine
1602314400.descr: Classic British sitcom following the misadventures of a trio of elderly men from a Yorkshire village who never tire of playing tricks on their fellow townspeople. The series is Britain's longest-running comedy programme and has received many praises for its family-friendly humour and portrayal of older people.

1602316200.title: Last of the Summer Wine
1602316200.descr: Clegg is writing his memoirs, but is having trouble remembering people's names; Clegg, Truly and Billy meet a man who wants to sail to Ilkley in an inflatable swan, unfortunately it has developed a puncture which Entwistle repairs; Clegg climbs a tree so he can see the church clock, unfortunately he gets stuck; Tom and Entwistle try to cheer Smiler up after he has been dumped by Hermione.

1602323400.title: Doctors
1602323400.descr: British medical soap drama about the staff in an NHS doctor's surgery, along with their family and friends in the fictional town of Letherbridge, West Midlands. As well as dealing with patients in and out of the surgery, the staff have constant problems of their own, making it almost impossible to separate work life from personal life.

1602327900.title: Still Open All Hours
1602327900.descr: Still Open All Hours really is STILL Open All Hours after all these years. The show makes its grand return after almost thirty years off the air. It follows Granville who has now taken charge of the Arkwright's shop after the sad death of his uncle. A funny insight into the life of Granville who is following his late uncle's old ways with his unique selling techniques. British comedy.

1602350700.title: Doctor Who
1602350700.descr: Peter Capaldi, Pearl Mackie, Matt Lucas, Kieran Bew, Justin Salinger, Peter Caulfield. "Space – the final frontier. Final because it wants to kill us." Trapped on a space station with no oxygen, the Doctor, Bill and Nardole are horrified to discover the automated spacesuits keeping them alive are also trying to kill them!

1602353400.title: Doctor Who
1602353400.descr: 'The Veritas. The truth. Truth so true you can't live with it. Is that looking into hell ... or seeing the light?' Everyone who has ever read the Veritas has been found dead. In a forbidden library at the heart of the Vatican, the Pope urges the Doctor to read the ancient text but can he handle the truth?

1602356400.title: Bad Move
1602356400.descr: Steve (Jack Dee) and Nicky (Kerry Godliman) decide to move from Leeds to the countryside of Yorkshire, where they want to live a perfect, simple life away from the rat race. Soon they find out that the reality is more than disappointing. The house is in a bad condition, the internet doesn't reach, they miss many amenities of every day life. And the neighbours can be really annoying.

1602357900.title: Friday Night Dinner
1602357900.descr: A family comedy about a Jewish family who meet for dinner every Friday night. The family includes mother Jackie, father Martin, and two sons Adam (Simon Bird) and Jonathan. The episodes consist of disruptions to the dinner by Adam and Jonathan arguing or by neighbor Jim Bell (Mark Heap.) It began just a year after the show The Inbetweeners finished, and worked as a new series for fans to watch.

1602359400.title: Live at the Apollo
1602359400.descr: Hammersmith Apollo Theatre hosts some of the biggest names in stand up comedy. Hosted by Jack Dee, performing his own sketches and introducing well known and loved acts such as Lee Mack, Michael McIntyre, Sean Lock and Sarah Millican. Running since September 2004, this showtime series is a classic comedy staple, drawing crowds in their staggering numbers to the theatre in West London, every year.
